%N A088121 Smallest prime obtained as a sum of n terms of a geometric progression + the common ratio, or 0 if no such terms exists. Smallest prime of the form (a +ar +ar^2 + ar^3 +... ) + r.
%C A088121 The ratio is required to be > 1.
%C A088121 For a(5), (1 + r + r^2 + r^3 + r^4) + r is composite. hence the first term of the geometric progression is >1. For a(5) a = 5 and r = 2. This is true For all odd n.
%e A088121 a(3) = (3+6+12) + 2 = 23.
%e A088121 a(4) = (1+2+4+8 ) + 2 = 17.
%e A088121 a(6) = (3+6+12+24+48+96) + 2= 191.
